body:
 13b83e6 (confirmed with bisect) broke the following use case (in doctrine plugin):

```php
<?php
// https://github.com/weirdan/doctrine-psalm-plugin/blob/master/stubs/EntityManagerInterface.phpstub

namespace Doctrine\ORM;

use Doctrine\Common\Persistence\ObjectManager;

interface EntityManagerInterface extends ObjectManager
{
    /**
     * @param class-string<T> $entityName
     * @param mixed           $id
     *
     * @return T|null
     *
     * @template T
     */
    public function getReference(string $entityName, $id);
}
```

```php
<?php
// https://github.com/weirdan/doctrine-psalm-plugin/blob/master/stubs/EntityManager.phpstub

namespace Doctrine\ORM;

class EntityManager implements EntityManagerInterface
{
    /**
     * @template T
     * @param class-string<T> $entityName
     * @param mixed           $id
     *
     * @return null|T
     */
    public function getReference($entityName, $id)
    {
    }
}
```

```gherkin
  @EntityManager::getReference
  Scenario: Getting a reference
    Given I have the following code
      """
      <?php
      use Doctrine\ORM\EntityRepository;
      use Doctrine\ORM\EntityManager;
      interface I {}
      /**
       * @psalm-suppress InvalidReturnType
       * @return EntityManager
       */
      function em() {}
      atan(em()->getReference(I::class, 1));
      """
    When I run Psalm
    Then I see these errors
      | Type            | Message                                      |
      | InvalidArgument | Argument 1 of atan expects float, I provided |
    And I see no other errors
```

Instead of reporting the return type of `getReference()` as `I|null` Psalm now infers it as `I&(T:fn-doctrine\orm\entitymanagerinterface::getreference as object)|null` which doesn't make sense in the outer scope.

Apparently this affects stubs only, as I haven't been able to reproduce it on psalm.dev (futile attempt is here: https://psalm.dev/r/4c7cf7bb67)
